args:
Nyarlathotep, the being responsible for all
that has occurred, has been defeated, and the
people of Hethiwood safely returned to their
human forms. With the mystery solved,
the library returns to its silent vigil.

Behold the key which seals thee!
Now return to the netherrealm!
Qiso'era tsyuto'sena!
Qiso'era hotoso'naqo!
We are Chaos. Our quietus is our genesis.\nWe reign in twilight; the dark nightmare\nof a stillborn sun.

We manifest the Ancient One's Emissary.
We are multifarious. Multifarious forms.
Multifarious names. Multifaaaaar...
Mul...tiiiii...faaaaar...
This damn thing can't even die\nwithout being creepy.
Are those the people of Hethiwood?
With the cause of their suffering defeated,\nthey have been returned to normal.

To use magic that dies with the user
is the most basic of errors. Our enemy
would have been better served to wield
a finer form of sorcery.
Heinwald? This is the part where you\nshut up and just be happy we won.
Jeez my knees, what a relief!
Whatever you say to this Lathna,\nshe will not understand.
Doesn't change the fact that this\nis an auspicious occasion.
I'm not sure what happened...\nbut I was so scared.
I was in such pain and...so afraid.\nDid you all save me?
Well, I'll be. Always nice to get a little\ngirl's smile as an unexplected reward.
Well, now that the villagers are safe,\nwe need to figure out what we're\ngoing to do about this library.
Can we not seal it up as it was originally?
Have you all taken leave of your senses?!\nWhy must we part with the library at all?!

And what exactly is the danger here?!
I simply cannot bear to lose such a
pleasa... Er, such a VALUABLE trove
of books and knowledge!
I knew this was just about your curiosity.\n...C'mon, Heinwald. It's time to go.
Quit acting like a baby and come... Grrr!\nLet go of the damn bookshelf already!
*sigh* He hardly seems like the same\nman who helped us track down and\ndefeat the evil of Nyarlathotep.
Well, he's the sort of person who steps up\nwhen he needs too, I suppose.
Fine! If you're all so eager to ＂deal with＂\nthis library and seal it away, I would hear\nhow exactly you plan to do this.
Just like it was to begin with, I suppose.

The magic that sealed this library was
skillful, delicate, and extremely complex.
I doubt any of you are capable of faithfully
replicating such a spell.
Are you saying you won't help with that?\nBecause I have ways of gaining your\ncooperation, believe me.
Do not misunderstand me—I will help you.\nHowever, I currently lack the ability to\nwield the magic required.
If, however, I could research the books\nhere, I'm sure I could figure it out.\nSo then, what say you?
Why do I feel like we're all being\ntaken advantage of here?
What do you think, Prince? After all,\nyou stand to be most inconvenienced\nby the presence of this library.
Well, with Nyarlathotep defeated,\nthe most urgent crisis has passed.
Although the other one is still around.
I am Emissary. I have neither duty\nnor motive to seek sacrifice.
This Nyarlathotep has a different way of\nthinking. We can at least rest assured\nhe will turn no one into a book.
In that case, I suppose it's fine\nto leave things as they are.
Excellent! ...You know, it wouldn't be an\noverstatement to say your generosity is\nwhat resolved this entire incident.
Well you certainly changed your tune fast.\nYou were all grumbles a minute ago.
I'm serious. It was your kindness that\nmade the false Lathna negligent.
Had that not happened, it would not have\nused such a method of trying to get you to\nread the spell.
Not to be rude, but it sounds like you're\nsaying we are a bunch of simple dullards\nwho were easy to trap.

Heh. I suppose there's a little truth in that.
Still, I'd rather believe in someone than
doubt them. That's why we ended up
on top in this case, right?
Life is just a series of doubts. That said,\nif you ONLY doubt others, you'll never\ntake a chance or meet a new friend!
Hail, stranger. What do you seek?
Only the truth. And to that end,\nI'd like to make an inquiry of you.

Uncertain truth. Doubtless fiction.
A mirage upon a distant shore.
One utterance which wavers between
two sides in its conveyance.
I shall determine for myself whether\nor not your words are worthy of belief.

You said you were ＂both atheneum and
keeper,＂ and that you ＂looked grievously
upon your shuttered shelves.＂  This means
you missed your freedom.

You also said, ＂We are fettered, trapped
by quailing wings.＂ I think those wings
were actually the Nyarlathotep that had
transformed into Lathna.
But now the quailing wings that freed the\nlibrary from its seal have disappeared,\nwhich is good news for you.
This was what you were seeking.\n...Wasn't it?
All of us—even the other Nyarlathotep—\ndid your bidding without realizing it.
Reckoning. Capacity. You ken Our words,\nand by doing so, Our meaning.
You should not fathom thus, yet do.\nYou are a quandary of being.
...Being? You mean my existence?\nWhile it's true I might understand\nyou, what's the problem with that?
You ken Our words and meaning.\nThose who fathom the abyss\nare beguiled by such.
